+(U1) Soundness.
+If (unify τ₁ τ₂) = Unifiable θ, then θ(τ₁) ≡ θ(τ₂). θ is a most general
+unifier for τ₁ and τ₂.
+
+(U2) Completeness.
+If (unify ξ₁ ξ₂) = SurelyApart,
+then there exists no substitution θ such that θ(ξ₁) ≡ θ(ξ₂).
